      "rationale": "Code verification was performed using the Method of Manufactured Solutions (MMS) for the incompressible Navier-Stokes equations with non-Newtonian viscosity on three systematically refined meshes. Observed order of convergence p = 1.97 (theoretical second order) for velocity and p = 1.88 for pressure, confirming correct implementation of the discretization scheme. Additionally, benchmark problems from the FDA Critical Path CFD validation study (Stewart et al. 2012) were reproduced within published tolerances. All MMS test cases are archived in the SVR and traceable to solver version 2023R2.",
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/ac/numerical-code-verification",
        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "description": "MMS convergence order within 10% of theoretical order for all primary variables on at least three mesh levels. Benchmark reproduction within published tolerances for FDA nozzle and pump reference cases. Achieved: observed order 1.97 vs theoretical 2.0 (1.5% deviation), FDA benchmark within 5% of published results."
      }
    },
