      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 5,
      "rationale": "A systematic mesh refinement study was conducted on four mesh levels (1.2M, 3.8M, 9.6M, and 22.4M hexahedral-dominant cells) at the nominal operating point. Grid Convergence Index (GCI) was computed per Roache (1998) using the fine-grid solution as reference. GCI_fine = 1.8% for NIH and 2.9% for pressure rise, both well below the 5% acceptance threshold. The 9.6M mesh was selected as the production mesh based on the asymptotic convergence ratio (r = 1.001, confirming grid-independent solution). Wall y+ values were maintained below 1.0 on all impeller and volute surfaces to resolve the viscous sublayer without wall functions.",
