      "rationale": "Experimental test conditions were matched to CFD boundary conditions with high fidelity. Inlet velocity profiles were measured by PIV and applied as spatially varying Dirichlet boundary conditions in CFD. Blood analog fluid (glycerol-water mixture, 36% by mass) was characterized for viscosity at 37°C using a cone-and-plate rheometer; measured viscosity curve was fit to Carreau-Yasuda model (R² = 0.998) and applied identically in CFD. Temperature was controlled to 37 ± 0.3°C in experiments. Rotational speed was measured by optical encoder to ±1 rpm. Fluid temperature, hematocrit surrogate concentration, and inlet turbulence intensity were all documented and matched between experiment and simulation.",
