      "rationale": "The primary QoI is the Normalized Index of Hemolysis (NIH, g/100L), which is the regulatory-accepted metric for blood pump hemolysis assessment per ASTM F1841 and ISO 10993-4. The relative hemolysis index (RH = NIH_device / NIH_predicate) directly maps to the regulatory decision criterion (RH < 1.0). Secondary QoIs include pump pressure rise (validated against pump curve) and velocity field (validated against PIV), providing corroborating evidence of model fidelity. The QoI chain from CFD stress tensor → hemolysis power law → NIH integration → RH comparison is fully documented and traceable to the regulatory submission claim.",
