      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "rationale": "Model form selection is justified through a structured model form uncertainty analysis. The Giersiepen-Wurzinger hemolysis power law (α = 3.62×10⁻⁷, β = 2.416, γ = 0.785) was selected based on a literature review of 8 candidate hemolysis models and a Bayesian model comparison using the experimental NIH dataset. The selected model achieved the highest marginal likelihood (Bayes factor > 10 vs next-best model). Turbulence was modeled using SST k-ω with low-Reynolds-number corrections, selected based on sensitivity analysis showing < 5% NIH sensitivity to turbulence model choice between SST k-ω and k-ε realizable at this Reynolds number range. Non-Newtonian effects were confirmed significant (< 8% NIH difference with Newtonian assumption) and retained in the production model.",
